U.S. OPEN
September 5, 1993
Cedric Pioline
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 
Q.  Did you feel like you were playing a ghost?
 
CEDRIC PIOLINE:  Not really.  I mean, I think he is not playing like five years ago or six years ago, but he played not so bad and got a lot of experience, but like he didn't play too many matches.  At the important moment he is making some mistakes, but it is not like a ghost. 
 

Q. Apart from making errors in important moments, was there anything else that you felt was a sign of his not playing for a long time; any other aspect of his game, or his --
 
CEDRIC PIOLINE:  Yeah, at the beginning he was a little bit nervous.  He made some easy mistake and so he then take the ball too early, you know, when he get some occasion to come in, so I thought he was a little bit nervous; not comfortable. 
 

Q. What do you feel about your chances at this event at this point?
 
CEDRIC PIOLINE:  I mean, I don't know, the fourth round I think I am going to play Courier, Courier/MaliVai, never-- I never beat him.  It is a good match for me.  In the big tournament, I do my best and I play well and I can play a little bit better, so maybe it can be close. 
 

Q. Thank you.      


